99; font-weight: bold;"> stifling and fall in love with someone else. </span></span></strong><br /> <strong><span style="font-family: Trebuchet MS; color: #000099;"><span style="color: #000099; font-weight: bold;"> Unlike the days of the past </span></span></strong><br /> <strong><span style="font-family: Trebuchet MS; color: #000099;"><span style="color: #000099; font-weight: bold;"> when only death could do you apart.</span></span></strong><strong><span style="font-family: Trebuchet MS; color: #000066;"><span style="color: #000066; font-weight: bold;"> <br /> </span></span></strong><strong><span style="font-family: Trebuchet MS; color: #ff9900; font-size: medium;"><span style="font-size: 13.5pt; color: #ff9900; font-weight: bold;"><br /> Does that mean the present generation </span></span></strong><br /> <strong><span style="font-family: Trebuchet MS; color: #ff9900; font-size: medium;"><span style="font-size: 13.5pt; color: #ff9900; font-weight: bold;"> is less sincere   when it says ''I love you''? </span></span></strong><br /> <strong><span style="font-family: Trebuchet MS; color: #000099;"><span style="color: #000099; font-weight: bold;"> I doesn''t think so.</span></span></strong> <br /> <strong><span style="font-family: Trebuchet MS; color: #ff9900; font-size: x-small;"><span style="font-size: 10pt; color: #ff9900; font-weight: bold;"> "</span></span></strong><strong><span style="font-family: Trebuchet MS; color: #ff9900; font-size: medium;"><span style="font-size: 13.5pt; color: #ff9900; font-weight: bold;">They no longer say   it to express a commitment</span></span></strong><strong><span style="font-family: Trebuchet MS; color: #ff9900; font-size: x-small;"><span style="font-size: 10pt; color: #ff9900; font-weight: bold;">. </span></span></strong><br /> <strong><span style="font-family: Trebuchet MS; color: #ff9900; font-size: medium;"><span style="font-size: 13.5pt; color: #ff9900; font-weight: bold;"> I believe they   mean it when they say it,"</span></